*Summary*

At the moment, if a user is not a member of the groups *administrators* and *jira-administrators* and try to enable the Slack Integration into JIRA, they get the following error message:

{code}
Slack integration add-on error: something went wrong while updating instance
Please, contact support or try again later.
{code}

*Suggestion*

For the users' perspective, it would be great if the error message shows more details about it, something like:

{code}
Slack integration add-on error: something went wrong while updating instance
Please, review your account privileges and try again, or contact support.
{code}

h3. Problem Definition
If an image is too wide to fit the comment section it will add a horizontal slider. It would be better for images to fit the width.

h3. Suggested Solutions
Implement a CSS for images in comments to have the max-width property set so that large images do not extend outside of the container.

{code}.action-body image {
max-width: 100%;
}
{code}

